The paper deals with a robotics problem of sorting multiple objects, which involves planning and control. Therefore, cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely sub-category. The paper proposes a Monte Carlo tree search algorithm with a task-specific heuristic function, which falls under the scope of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The algorithm also involves image processing and object recognition, which are related to cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also discusses the use of sensors and feedback control, which are relevant to cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper evaluates the algorithm's performance on various simulated tasks, which is related to cs.LG (Machine Learning).
